 from Africa to Europe. By engaging with the recordings alongside written sources, photographs, and artworks depicting the speakers, Hoffmann personalizes speakers from present-day Senegal, Somalia, Togo, and Congo. Knowing by Ear includes transcriptions of numerous recordings of spoken and sung texts, revealing acoustic archives as significant yet under-researched sources for recovering the historical speaking positions of colonized subjects and listen to the acoustic echo of colonial knowledge production.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAfricanszGermanyxHistoryy20th centuryxArchival resources. 0aPrisoners of warzGermanyxHistoryy20th centuryxArchival resources. 0aPrisoners' songszGermany. 0aSound recordings in ethnologyzGermany. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xPrisoners and prisons, German. 7aHISTORY / Africa / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311135689140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478059028?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478059028423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478059028/original  a978-3-11-135689-1  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles